<span id="freeTextContainer15388777777726077832">Volume I: This book is awesome. I&apos;ll fill in the review once I&apos;ve read the other three volumes.<br/><br/>Volume II: The stuff of legends. Battle, intrigue, strategy, poetry, honor ..<br/><br/>Volume III: I almost lost interest in the first half, but was well-rewarded by the developments that followed.<br/><br/>Volume IV: &quot;The empire long divided, must unite; long united, must divide.&quot; The conclusion kept me guessing up to the end. In this volume it was sad that Kongming died without reaching his goal, and sadder that the chi</span>
  <span id="freeText15388777777726077832" style="display:none">Volume I: This book is awesome. I'll fill in the review once I've read the other three volumes.<br /><br />Volume II: The stuff of legends. Battle, intrigue, strategy, poetry, honor ..<br /><br />Volume III: I almost lost interest in the first half, but was well-rewarded by the developments that followed.<br /><br />Volume IV: "The empire long divided, must unite; long united, must divide." The conclusion kept me guessing up to the end. In this volume it was sad that Kongming died without reaching his goal, and sadder that the children of some of my favorite heroes were so lacking in virtue. <br />But chills ran across my body as I read the final poem summarizing over 100 years of myth and history related by hundreds of characters over thousands of pages and which I took almost a year to read.</span>
